# Session [18] – Network+

## Main Topics
- Tracert va Ping dar Windows chist?  
- Tarze estefadeh  
- TTL (Time To Live) chist va chetor kar mikonad  

## Flashback – Tracert & Ping Basics
- **Ping** = test connectivity be yek IP ya domain  
- **Tracert** = peygiri masir packet az device shoma ta destination  
- TTL = meghdar zendeghi packet (chand hop mitavanad beravad)  

## Explanation

### Ping
- Command: `ping [IP address]`  
- Check mikonad device dar network dastresi dare ya na  
- Response time (ms) ro mide  

### Tracert
- Command: `tracert [IP address]`  
- Har hop (router) ro neshan mide ke packet az koja gozar kard  
- Masir network ro visualize mikonad  

### TTL (Time To Live)
- Har packet dar IP header TTL dare  
- Har router → TTL minus 1  
- Agar TTL = 0 beshe → packet discard mishavad  
- Prevent kardan looping dar network  

### Example
| Command | Output | Description |
|---------|--------|------------|
| ping 8.8.8.8 | Reply from 8.8.8.8: bytes=32 time=20ms TTL=128 | Check connectivity |
| tracert 8.8.8.8 | 1 192.168.1.1 → 2 10.0.0.1 → … | Masir packet ro neshan mide |

